The '''kikau''' or '''western wattled honeyeater''' ('''''Foulehaio procerior''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[honeyeater]] family Meliphagidae. It was considered conspecific with the [[Fiji wattled honeyeater]] and the [[Polynesian wattled honeyeater]].

The species is [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Viti Levu]], [[Ovalau]] and the islands of the [[Yasawa|Yasawa Archipelago]] in [[Fiji]].
Its natural [[habitat]]s are tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s, tropical [[mangrove]] forests, and tropical moist [[montane forest]].

